obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (34287)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00020_191912_1523343031904&sectionId=34287&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00020_191912_1523343031904
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Poisons Act, 1919.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(2) It extends to the whole of India:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall not apply to the State of Jammu and Kashmir* except to the extent to which the`
  line `provisions of this Act relate to the importation into India of any specified poison.]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1958, s. 2, for the former sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `*. Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (34288)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Power of the State Government to regulate possession for sale and sale of any poison.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. The words "Subject to the control of the G.G. in C" rep. by the A.O. 1937.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00020_191912_1523343031904&sectionId=34288&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00020_191912_1523343031904
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `^1*** The State Government may by rule regulate within the whole or any part of the territories under its`
  line `administration the possession for sale and the sale, whether wholesale or retail, of any specified poison.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the grant of licences to possess any specified poison for sale, wholesale or retail, and fixing of`
  line `the fee (if any) to be charged for such licences ;`
  line
  line `(b) the classes of persons to whom alone such licences may be granted ;`
  line
  line `(c) the classes of persons to whom alone any such poison may be sold ;`
  line
  line `(d) the maximum quantity of any such poison which may be sold to any one person ;`
  line
  line `(e) the maintenance by vendors of any such poison of registers of sales, the particulars to be`
  line `entered in such registers, and the inspection of the same ;`
  line
  line `(f) the safe custody of such poisons and the labelling of the vessels, packages or coverings in`
  line `which any such poison is sold or possessed for sale ; and`
  line
  line `(g) the inspection and examination of any such poison when possessed for sale by any such`
  line vendor.
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (34289)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to prohibit importation into the States of any poison except under licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00020_191912_1523343031904&sectionId=34289&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00020_191912_1523343031904
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, prohibit, except under and in accordance`
  line `with the conditions of a licence, the importation into ^1`
  line `[India] ^2`
  line `[across any customs frontier^3`
  line `defined by the`
  line `Central Government] of any specified poison, and may by rule regulate the grant of licences.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Sub. By Act 47 of 1958, s. 3, for "the States".`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `3. For definition of the customs frontiers of India, see Gazette of India, 1955, Pt. II, sec. 3, p. 1521.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (34290)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Power to regulate possession of any poison in certain areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. The words “subject to the control of the G.G. in C.” rep by the A.O. 1937.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00020_191912_1523343031904&sectionId=34290&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00020_191912_1523343031904
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government ^1`
  line ***
  line `may by rule regulate on the possession of any specified poison in any local area in which the use of such`
  line `poison for the purpose of committing murder or mischief by poisoning cattle appears to it to be of such`
  line `frequent occurrence as to render restrictions on the possession thereof desirable.`
  line
  line `(2) In making any rule under sub-section (1), the State Government may direct that any breach`
  line `thereof shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine`
  line `which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both, together with confiscation of the poison in`
  line `respect of which the breach has been committed, and of the vessels, packages or coverings in which the`
  line `same is found.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (34291)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Presumption as to specified poisons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00020_191912_1523343031904&sectionId=34291&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00020_191912_1523343031904
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Any substance specified as a poison in a rule made or`
  line `notification issued under this Act shall be deemed to be a poison for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (34292)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Penalty for unlawful importation, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00020_191912_1523343031904&sectionId=34292&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00020_191912_1523343031904
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever—`
  line
  line `(a) commits a breach of any rule made under section 2, or`
  line
  line `(b) imports ^1`
  line `*** without a licence ^2`
  line `[into ^3`
  line `[India] across a customs frontier^4`
  line `defined by the Central`
  line `Central Government] any poison the importation of which is for the time being restricted under`
  line `section 3, or`
  line
  line `(c) breaks any condition of a licence for the importation of any poison granted to him under`
  line `section 3,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable, —`
  line
  line `(i) on a first conviction, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months, or with`
  line `fine which may extend to five hundred rupees, or with both, and`
  line
  line `(ii) on a second or subsequent conviction, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six`
  line `months, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Any poison in respect of which an offence has been committed under this section, together with`
  line `the vessels, packages or coverings in which the same is found, shall be liable to confiscation.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words “into British India” rep. ibid.`
  line
  line `2. Ins.by the A.O.1937.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 47 of 1958, s. 3, for “the States”.`
  line
  line `4. For definition of the customs frontiers of India, see Gazette of India, 1955, Pt. II, sec. 3, p. 1521.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (34293)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to issue search warrants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1 See now the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00020_191912_1523343031904&sectionId=34293&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00020_191912_1523343031904
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The District Magistrate, the Sub-divisional Magistrate and,`
  line `in a presidency-town, the Commissioner of Police, may issue a warrant for the search of any place in`
  line `which he has reason to believe or to suspect that any poison is possessed or sold in contravention of this`
  line `Act or any rule thereunder, or that any poison liable to confiscation under this Act is kept or concealed.`
  line
  line `(2) The person to whom the warrant is directed may enter and search the place in accordance`
  line `therewith, and the provisions of the ^1 Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), relating to searchwarrants shall, as far as may be, be deemed to apply to the execution of the warrant.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (34294)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title Rules.
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00020_191912_1523343031904&sectionId=34294&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00020_191912_1523343031904
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) In addition to any other power to make rules hereinbefore conferred ^1`
  line `*** the State`
  line `Government may make rules generally to carry out the purposes and objects of this Act ^2`
  line [except
  line `section 3]`
  line
  line `(2) Every power to make rules conferred by this Act shall be subject to the condition of the rules`
  line `being made after previous publication.`
  line
  line `(3) All rules made by the Central Government or by the State Government under this Act shall be`
  line `published in the ^3`
  line `[Official Gazette] and on such publication shall have effect as if enacted in this Act.`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(4) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule. rule.`
  line
  line `(5) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made, before the State Legislature.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words “subject to the control of the G.G. in C.” rep by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `2. Ins.by the A.O.1937.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, para 4, for “Gazette of India or the local Official Gazette , as the case may be”, Strictly the`
  line `substitution would read “Official Gazette or the Official Gazette, as the case may be” but the last nine words have been omitted`
  line `as being obviously redundant.`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and Sch. (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (34295)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00020_191912_1523343031904&sectionId=34295&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00020_191912_1523343031904
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in this Act or in any licence granted or rule made s thereunder shall extend`
  line `to, or interfere with, anything done in good faith in the exercise of his profession as such by a medical or`
  line `veterinary practitioner.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything hereinbefore contained, the State Government may ^1`
  line `*** by general or`
  line `special order declare that all or any of the provisions of this Act ^2`
  line `[except section 3] shall be deemed not to`
  line `to apply to any article or class of articles of commerce specified in such order, or to any poison or class of`
  line `poisons used for any purpose so specified.`
  line
  line `(3) The authority on which any power to make rules under this Act is conferred may, by general or`
  line `special order, either wholly or partially—`
  line
  line `(a) exempt from the operation of any such rules, or`
  line
  line `(b) exclude from the scope of the exemption provided by sub-section (1),`
  line
  line `any person or class of persons either generally or in respect of any poisons specified in the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words “in its discretion” rep. by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `2. Ins., ibid..`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (34296)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title [Repealed.].
  content `[Repeal of Act 1 of 1904.] Rep.by the Repealing Act, 1927 (12 of 1927).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00020_191912_1523343031904&sectionId=34296&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00020_191912_1523343031904
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
